\c 25
\s1 Offering for the Holy Tent
\p
\v 1 The LORD said to Moses,
\v 2 “Tell the nation of Israel to bring offerings to Me. Receive offerings from everyone whose hearts are moved to give.
\v 3 These are the offerings that you may receive from them:
\li2 gold, silver, bronze,
\li2
\v 4 blue, purple, and red wool threads, fine linen, goat’s hair,
\li2
\v 5 male goat skins dyed red, fine skin, acacia wood,
\li2
\v 6 olive oil for light, spices to be added into anointing oil and for burning incense,
\li2
\v 7 onyx stones and other prescious stones to be set on the ephod\f + \fr 25:7 \fk ephod \ft See the note about ephod on Exo. 28:6.\f* and on the breast piece.
\p
\v 8 “Say to them that they have to build a special holy place for Me for Me to live among them.
\v 9 You have to lead them to make this Holy Tent and its furnitures exactly according to all patterns that I will show to you.”
\s1 Ark of the Covenant
\p
\v 10 “ Make an ark from acacia wood, with length 114cm, width 69cm, and height 69 cm.\f + \fr 25:10 \fk cm measurements \ft Literally, “with length 2.5 cubits, width 1.5 cubits, and height 1.5 cubits.” 1 cubit = approximately 45 cm.\f*
\v 11 Layer the outer and inner part of that ark with pure gold, and make a golden frame for the top part.
\v 12 To carry it, make four golden bracelets and attach them on the sides on its four feet, with two bracelets on each side.
\v 13 Make a stick of acacia wood and layer it with gold.
\v 14 Insert the stick on the bracelets that are on the two sides of the ark so that the ark can be carried.
\v 15 The sticks must remain attached on the ark bracelets, and may not be detached.
\v 16 You have to put into the ark the two stone tablets written with My commands, which I will give you.
\p
\v 17 “Make an ark cover from pure gold with length 114cm and width 69 cm.
\v 18-19 Make also two statues in the shape of a winged creature\f + \fr 25:7 \fk winged creature \ft The winged created made from gold that is meant in here is cherubb or winged angels that are often associated with closeness to God.\f*from forged/hammered gold on the two ends of that ark cover, one on each end. The two statues of winged creature must be one part with the ark cover.
\v 20 The two winged creature must be facing each other, with face directed towards the ark cover, and spreading their wings upwards so that they cover the ark cover.
\v 21 Put in the stone tablets written with the law of God that I gave to you into that ark, and put the ark cover over the ark.”
\s1 Table for serving bread for the LORD
\p
\v 22 “I will meet you there, and from between the two winged creatures that is on top of the cover of the Covenant Ark, I will give all My commands to you to be conveyed to the nation of Israel.
\v 23 Make a table from acacia wood with length 91 cm, width 46 cm and height 69 cm.
\v 24 Layer the table with pure gold, and attach a golden frame around it.
\v 25 The frame is 8 cm wide and on the sides of the frame make a rim from gold.
\v 26 Make four gold bracelets and attach those four bracelets on the four corners where there are four table feet.
\v 27 Those bracelets must be attached near the frame as a place to attach the sticks, which are used to carry the table.
\v 28 Make those sticks from acacia wood and layer them with gold. Carry that table using those sticks.
\v 29 Make large plates, spoons, pitchers, and bowls to be used in wine offering. Make all these from pure gold.
\v 30 Let the serving bread for Me always be on top of this table.”
\s1 Lampstand
\p
\v 31 “Make branched lampstand from pure gold. The lampstand must be made from gold that is completely formed from the same piece— including the base, stem, petals, and flowers.
\v 32 Make the lampstand with six branches, three branches on the left side and three branches on the right side.
\v 33 Every branch must be decorated with three decorations with a shape like almond flowers, each with petals and flowers.
\v 34 On the lampstand itself there must be four decorations in the shape of almond flowers, each with petals and flowers.
\v 35 Make also almond petals under the six branches that are divided to three pairs, that comes out from the base of the lampstand.
\v 36 Those petals and branches must be made from one piece of pure gold.
\v 37 Make seven lamps and place those on them, so that the lamp lights up the area in front of it.
\v 38 The tongs/tweezers and their trays must also be made from pure gold.
\v 39 About 34 kg of pure gold is needed to make that branched lampstand along with its equipments.
\p
\v 40 “Make sure (you) make everything according to the pattern that was shown to you on that mountain.”